						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Kulasēkharadēva. Year 20 (13th cent. A.D.).</hi></p>						

						<p>In two fragments. The first fragment is much damaged and seems to record a tax free grant of 3 <hi rend="italic">vēlis</hi> of land to the goddess in the temple of Tiruviḍavandai as <hi rend="italic">tirunāmattukkāṇi.</hi> The second fragment mentions the distribution of sacred food offering in the temple.</p>						

